On Memorial Day, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. issued a proclamation honoring the patriots who sacrificed their lives in service to America, freedom, and justice. He emphasized that these individuals defended the Constitution and democracy, and their bravery ensured our freedom. The President recognized the pride of those who serve in the United States Armed Forces and their dedication to a cause greater than themselves. He expressed gratitude for the fallen heroes and their contributions to a more perfect Union. The President also called for prayers and reflection on this day, urging Americans to observe a National Moment of Remembrance at 3:00 p.m. local time. He requested that flags be flown at half-staff until noon and encouraged citizens to display the flag at half-staff from their homes. President Biden concluded by honoring the memories of the fallen heroes and their everlasting impact on our hearts and the nation.